---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Janis Rozenblats — founder, product leader, operator." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="about-header">
				<div class="avatar">JR</div>
				<h1>Janis Rozenblats</h1>
				<p class="tagline">Entrepreneur, founder, and product leader. I build companies, frameworks, and products — then write about what actually works when scaling teams.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="prose">
				<h2>Background</h2>
				<p>
					I've been building and scaling companies for 20 years across 8 countries. At 19, I started my first web agency in Denmark. Then I founded <strong>Mailigen</strong> — an email marketing platform I grew from 4 people in a 12sqm office to a team of 40 and a few million in annual revenue.
				</p>
				<p>
					Mailigen was acquired by <strong>Pipedrive</strong> in 2020. I spent 4 years there as VP of Product through a Vista Private Equity acquisition — learning what happens when a startup operating system meets institutional scale.
				</p>
				<p>
					Most recently, I led product and services at <strong>Aerones</strong> — a wind industry robotics company — where I drove organizational transformation, built AI-powered software products, and shaped the strategy for scaling robotic services across continents.
				</p>
				<p>
					Today I write for founders and senior operators who are scaling from 20 to 200+ people — the phase where most teams quietly break. I bring 20 years of building, breaking, and rebuilding operating systems to help leaders see what their teams won't say out loud.
				</p>

				<h2>Why This Site</h2>
				<p>
					Scaling from 20 to 200 people is where most founders break. Not because they lack talent or vision, but because the operating system that got them to 20 doesn't work at 50.
				</p>
				<p>
					I've lived this — as a founder, as a VP inside a PE-backed scale-up, and as a product leader inside a hardware-meets-software company. Now I write about what actually worked, build tools that help leaders read their teams, and share the frameworks I wish I'd had earlier.
				</p>
				<p>
					No theory. No frameworks-for-frameworks-sake. Just what holds up when the stakes are real.
				</p>

				<h2>Connect</h2>
				<p>
					<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/janisr/">LinkedIn</a> — I'm most active here.
				</p>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.about-header {
		padding: 3em 0 2.5em;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
		margin-bottom: 2.5em;
	}
	.avatar {
		width: 64px;
		height: 64px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		background: rgba(201, 165, 90, 0.1);
		border: 2px solid var(--accent);
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		font-size: 1.2em;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--accent);
		margin-bottom: 1.5em;
	}
	h1 {
		font-size: 2em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}
	.tagline {
		color: var(--text-muted);
		font-size: 1.05em;
		line-height: 1.7;
		max-width: 540px;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.prose h2 {
		margin-top: 2.5em;
		margin-bottom: 0.75em;
		font-size: 1.25em;
	}
	.prose p {
		color: var(--text-muted);
		line-height: 1.8;
	}
	.prose strong { color: var(--text); }
	.prose a {
		color: var(--accent);
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-underline-offset: 3px;
	}
</style>
